text: Grandma got these for my daughter when she was about 9 months old.  The pros: the bugs are cute and bright, made of durable yet soft plastic and my daughter loves them.  The cons: baby cannot possibly detach or reattach the bugs on her own as it takes a little muscle to do it.  So, sometimes baby gets frustrated.  Also, it's not clear what types of bugs certain of these creatures are supposed to be.  Still, lots of fun for my little one.
author: LA Mommy
